  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Change in frailty status</measure>
    <time_frame>Two months</time_frame>
    <description>Frailty will be determined by Frailty Phenotype (FP) or Short Physical Performance Battery (SPPB) scores. FP is determined by the presence of 3 or more of the following: slowness (measured by gait speed), exhaustion (measured via self-report), weakness (measured by hand grip strength), low physical activity level (measured via self-report), and wasting (measured via self-report or by tracking changes in weight). The SPPB consists of a gait speed test, balance testing, and repeated chair stands. A score less than or equal to 10 will be considered frail.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <number_of_arms>2</number_of_arms>
